OL,3,CVotes being counted in crucial
OL,4,Celections for Sir Keir Starmer's
OL,5,Cpremiership
OL,7,FGreater Manchester Mayor Andy Burnham,
OL,8,Fwho is said to have a plan to return
OL,9,Fto Westminster within weeks, has
OL,10,Fdropped out of giving a speech on
OL,11,FFriday morning.
OL,13,FMr Burnham had been expected to
OL,14,Faddress the second annual Festival of
OL,15,FChildhood in Manchester on the morning
OL,16,Fafter the elections, but on Thursday
OL,17,Fevening organisers said he had been
OL,18,Freplaced by Caroline Simpson, group
OL,19,Fchief executive of the Greater
OL,20,FManchester Combined Authority.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778205813
OL,3,CVotes being counted in crucial
OL,4,Celections for Sir Keir Starmer's
OL,5,Cpremiership
OL,7,FBut Mr Lammy insisted Sir Keir would
OL,8,Fremain in office, pointing to poor
OL,9,Flocal election results seen by other
OL,10,Fprime ministers who went on to win re-
OL,11,Felection.
OL,13,FHe said: "I remember, after our huge
OL,14,Fvictory in 1997, a very bad set of
OL,15,Felection results for Tony Blair in
OL,16,F1999.
OL,18,F"David Cameron lost successive local
OL,19,Felections when he was in office, but
OL,20,Fwent on to win the 2015 election.
OL,26,@uD@JOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778205813
OL,3,CVotes being counted in crucial
OL,4,Celections for Sir Keir Starmer's
OL,5,Cpremiership
OL,7,F"So it's not unusual to be given a
OL,8,Fmessage by the electorate at mid-term
OL,9,Felections."
OL,11,FMr Lammy also warned against playing
OL,12,F"pass the parcel" as the Tories did
OL,13,F"with leader after leader", telling
OL,14,Fthe BBC: "There are questions that we
OL,15,Fhave to answer, but.. there is no
OL,16,Fcircumstances in which the answer to
OL,17,Fthe questions that the British people
OL,18,Fare raising is to change the leader
OL,19,Fyet again."
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@KO]tD@AOUtD@QO]uD@AOUuD@ZO]vD@
OL,26,AJOU{D@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
