OL,3,CVotes being counted in crucial
OL,4,Celections for Sir Keir Starmer's
OL,5,Cpremiership
OL,7,FMeanwhile, Nigel Farage's Reform UK is
OL,8,Fset to make significant gains,
OL,9,Fbuilding on last year's local
OL,10,Felections that saw the party pick up
OL,11,Falmost 700 councillors and take
OL,12,Fcontrol of 10 authorities.
OL,14,FPointing to the fragmentation of the
OL,15,Ftraditional two-party duopoly,
OL,16,FReform's Zia Yusuf told the Press
OL,17,FAssociation: "We are used to, in our
OL,18,Flifetimes, Labour or the Conservative
OL,19,FParty winning majorities in general
OL,20,Felections with north of 40% of the
OL,21,Fvote.
OL,26,@yD@NOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1778205813
OL,3,CVotes being counted in crucial
OL,4,Celections for Sir Keir Starmer's
OL,5,Cpremiership
OL,7,F"And I think now, they are going to
OL,8,Fstruggle to get 40% between them, and
OL,9,FI don't think they're coming back. I
OL,10,Fthink the Greens are going to eat a
OL,11,Flot into Labour.
OL,13,F"I think Reform are going to eat a lot
OL,14,Finto Labour.
OL,16,F"Keep an eye on those Labour
OL,17,Fheartlands, you know, in the Red Wall.
OL,18,FThose areas, I think, are going to
OL,19,Fmove decisively turquoise. I think
OL,20,Fthere's going to be a turquoise wave
OL,21,Fthroughout that area."
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUxD@AOU}D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
